---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<Layout title="Why we chose Nx | Invent2025 Lab">
    <!-- Syntax Highlighting -->
    <link
        slot="head"
        rel="stylesheet"
        href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/11.9.0/styles/atom-one-dark.min.css"
    />
    <script
        slot="head"
        src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/11.9.0/highlight.min.js"
        is:inline></script>
    <script slot="head" is:inline>
        hljs.highlightAll();
    </script>

    <header slot="header" class="h-20 flex items-center justify-between mb-8">
        <a href="/blog" class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div
                class="w-8 h-8 bg-slate-800 rounded flex items-center justify-center text-slate-400 border border-slate-700 hover:border-white hover:text-white transition-colors"
            >
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-[20px]"
                    >arrow_back</span
                >
            </div>
            <span
                class="font-mono text-sm font-bold text-slate-500 hover:text-white transition-colors"
                >BACK TO LAB</span
            >
        </a>
    </header>

    <main>
        <article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
            <div class="not-prose mb-8 border-b border-border-dark pb-8">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                    <span
                        class="inline-flex items-center px-2 py-1 rounded text-[10px] font-mono font-bold bg-blue-500/10 text-blue-400 border border-blue-500/20"
                    >
                        ENGINEERING
                    </span>
                    <span class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-500"
                        >Jan 12, 2026</span
                    >
                </div>
                <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 leading-tight">
                    Why we chose Nx for Inviteathon's Monorepo?
                </h1>
            </div>

            <p class="lead text-xl text-slate-300">
                When we started Inviteathon, we knew it would grow beyond a
                single Angular app. We had an admin portal, a customer facing
                dashboard, and a set of shared UI libraries.
            </p>

            <h3>The Problem with Multi-Repo</h3>
            <p>
                Previously, we maintained separate repositories for each
                project. Sharing code meant publishing private NPM packages or
                using git submodules—both of which introduced friction.
            </p>

            <h3>Enter Nx</h3>
            <p>
                Nx allowed us to keep everything in a single repo while
                maintaining strict boundaries via
                <code>tags</code> in <code>nx.json</code>.
            </p>

            <pre><code class="language-json">&#123;
  "projects": &#123;
    "inviteathon-client": &#123; "tags": ["type:app", "scope:client"] &#125;,
    "inviteathon-admin": &#123; "tags": ["type:app", "scope:admin"] &#125;,
    "shared-ui": &#123; "tags": ["type:lib", "scope:shared"] &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

            <p>
                Now, if we try to import an admin-only library into the client
                app, the linter stops us immediately. CI/CD only runs for
                affected projects.
            </p>
        </article>
    </main>

    <footer
        slot="footer"
        class="mt-20 border-t border-border-dark pt-8 text-center"
    >
        <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs font-mono">
            © <span id="current-year">{currentYear}</span> Invent2025 Ltd.
        </p>
    </footer>
</Layout>
